comments: The Cavaliers inbound the ball within 5 seconds.
Westbrook (HOU) briefly places a hand/arm to Sexton's (CLE) front at the start of the drive.
During the rebound, Thompson (CLE) has a resting hand on Capela's (HOU) shoulder but does not apply force that impedes his ability to retrieve the ball.
Tucker (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Clarkson (CLE) during the drive.
Sexton (CLE) maintains a legal guarding position on Westbrook (HOU) at the end of the drive.
Thompson (CLE) is in the paint for about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Thompson (CLE) and Capela (HOU) engage and disengage during the rebound.
Thompson (CLE) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Thompson (CLE) makes marginal contact to Harden (HOU) after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Harden (HOU) makes marginal contact to Clarkson's (CLE) body at the end of the drive.
Porter Jr. (CLE) moves laterally into Westbrook's (HOU) path during the drive but the contact is marginal.
Love (CLE) makes contact to Capela's (HOU) head during his dunk.
Capela (HOU) cleanly dislodges the ball from Clarkson (CLE) during the inbound.
Clarkson (CLE) commits a take foul on Harden (HOU).
Sexton (CLE) makes marginal contact with Harden's (HOU) body during the inbound.
During the inbound, Harden (HOU) and Sexton (CLE) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Sexton (CLE) commits a take foul on Harden (HOU).
McLemore (HOU) is in a legal guarding position when Clarkson's (CLE) leg naturally extends on his jump shot and makes marginal contact to McLemore.
Porter Jr. (CLE) brushes his hand against Westbrook's (HOU) body as he goes for the steal.
